  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Sauté the sliced shallots in butter until crispy, then set aside.",
    "In a separate pan, sauté the mushrooms in butter until tender.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, and a pinch of salt.",
    "Add the flour to the egg mixture and whisk until smooth.",
    "Pour the egg mixture over the cooked mushrooms and stir to combine.",
    "Season the mixture with salt, pepper, and thyme.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a terrine dish and smooth the top.",
    "Bake for 25 minutes or until the terrine is set.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool.",
    "Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.",
    "Garnish with crispy shallots and serve with a squeeze of lime juice."
